WEBVTT

00:02.903 --> 00:06.006
Mail's here.
Let's see.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.641
Mom, you got
a new "Zoobook."

00:07.675 --> 00:09.277
Ooh, it's the penguin one.
[ Chuckles ]

00:13.081 --> 00:14.248
Looks like you boys
got a package.

00:15.549 --> 00:18.152
It's from cousin Hennessy
in Taiwan!

00:18.186 --> 00:20.588
Whoa!
It's a Tamagotchi!

00:20.621 --> 00:21.589
A Tama-what?

00:21.622 --> 00:24.058
Tamagotchi!
It's a virtual pet.

00:24.092 --> 00:25.759
They're the biggest toy
in Japan.

00:25.793 --> 00:27.761
They aren't even out
in America yet.

00:27.795 --> 00:29.163
Look.
He wrote us a note.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.232
"Hope you can take better care
of this than I could.

00:31.265 --> 00:32.566
Good luck.

00:32.600 --> 00:34.168
You're going to
need it."

00:34.202 --> 00:35.836
That sounds like
a warning.

00:35.869 --> 00:37.238
Or a cute alert.

00:37.271 --> 00:39.507
Look at it!
Look how cute it is!

00:39.540 --> 00:42.943
Last but not least,
there's one for you, Jessica.

00:42.976 --> 00:45.546
Uh-oh.

00:45.579 --> 00:47.181
**

00:47.215 --> 00:48.849
Notice for jury duty.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.218
[ Grandma Huang gasps ]

00:57.625 --> 00:58.792
* Fresh off the boat

00:58.826 --> 01:00.694
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:00.728 --> 01:02.696
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

01:02.730 --> 01:04.031
* Fresh off the boat

01:04.063 --> 01:06.300
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

01:06.334 --> 01:07.868
* But I know where I'm goin'

01:07.901 --> 01:10.271
* I'm fresh off the boat

01:11.272 --> 01:12.273
I don't understand.

01:12.306 --> 01:14.308
I've never
had to do jury duty before.

01:14.342 --> 01:15.476
How did they find me?

01:15.509 --> 01:17.311
Probably because you applied
for citizenship

01:17.345 --> 01:18.312
after your
green card expired.

01:18.346 --> 01:19.680
You're in
the system now.

01:23.284 --> 01:24.618
Well, I disagree.

01:24.652 --> 01:27.155
Doing jury duty is something
every American should do.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.889
We should give our Tamagotchi
a name

01:28.922 --> 01:30.758
that honors
the American justice system.

01:30.791 --> 01:32.126
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

01:32.160 --> 01:33.727
Jerry Orbach!Jerry Orbach!

01:33.761 --> 01:35.129
[ "Law & Order" notes play ]

01:35.163 --> 01:37.165
Evan, can I borrow
your Discman?

01:37.198 --> 01:38.899
I got spaghetti sauce
in mine.

01:38.932 --> 01:41.235
My Discman is just
for classical music

01:41.269 --> 01:43.437
and audio books,
not...

01:43.471 --> 01:45.406
**

01:45.439 --> 01:47.408
...Too "Dollar Sign" Hort.

01:47.441 --> 01:49.810
It's Too $hort, Evan.

01:49.843 --> 01:51.111
Too $hort.

01:51.145 --> 01:53.481
By the way,
happy anniversary, Eddie.

01:53.514 --> 01:56.450
I can't believe you and Allison
have been dating for a year.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.586
Thanks, man!
What kind of gift
did you get her?

01:58.619 --> 02:00.821
We don't get each other gifts.
We're beyond that.

02:00.854 --> 02:02.290
Happy anniversary,
Eddie!

02:02.323 --> 02:04.825
**

02:04.858 --> 02:07.195
You got me
a Flavor Flav necklace?

02:07.228 --> 02:09.430
I made it,
and it's not just a necklace.

02:09.463 --> 02:11.465
Open it.

02:11.499 --> 02:13.100
It's a clocket.
[locket]

02:13.133 --> 02:14.835
I blew up that picture
from our day at the carnival.

02:14.868 --> 02:16.670
Thanks, Allison.

02:16.704 --> 02:18.105
That's dope.

02:18.138 --> 02:20.040
Um, I got
you something, too.

02:23.511 --> 02:24.512
Is that a girl's butt?

02:24.545 --> 02:25.679
Yeah.

02:25.713 --> 02:27.648
In a martini glass,
so you know it's classy.

02:27.681 --> 02:29.450
This is already open!

02:29.483 --> 02:30.818
[ Scoffs ]
Okay, fine.

02:30.851 --> 02:32.019
I thought we said

02:32.052 --> 02:34.054
that we weren't going to
get each other gifts.

02:34.087 --> 02:35.856
We never said that.
Didn't we, though?

02:37.090 --> 02:38.326
[ Sighs ]
I'm sorry.

02:38.359 --> 02:39.560
Let me make it up
to you.

02:39.593 --> 02:41.695
How about we got to the mall
this weekend?

02:41.729 --> 02:43.297
We always
go to the mall.

02:43.331 --> 02:44.898
I want
to do something special.

02:44.932 --> 02:47.034
Let's go see
"Romeo and Juliet."

02:47.067 --> 02:50.037
It's a hip, modern remake
of Shakespeare's classic

02:50.070 --> 02:52.139
set in the town
of Verona Beach.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.041
And it has
Leonardo DiCaprio.

02:54.074 --> 02:56.710
Oh, Leo DiCaprio --
he's got star power.

02:56.744 --> 02:58.178
Get out of here,
Dave.
Sure thing.

02:58.212 --> 03:00.314
There's showings
at 7:00 and 9:30,

03:00.348 --> 03:02.283
and we're splitting
a box of Goobers.

03:09.590 --> 03:10.758
[ Sneezes ]

03:10.791 --> 03:11.759
**

03:11.792 --> 03:13.994
[ Yawns ]

03:14.027 --> 03:16.964
Smells like sadness.

03:18.232 --> 03:20.401
[ Sighs ]

03:20.434 --> 03:23.070
Welcome to
Orlando Superior Court.

03:23.103 --> 03:25.873
Some of you will have the good
fortune of serving on our jury,

03:25.906 --> 03:29.209
but first, I am legally required
to play you this video.

03:30.644 --> 03:34.882
[ Patriotic music plays ]

03:34.915 --> 03:36.850
Hello. I'm Gail O'Grady.

03:36.884 --> 03:39.753
Most of you know me
 as Donna Abandando,

03:39.787 --> 03:42.890
the brassy squad secretary
 on "NYPD Blue."

03:42.923 --> 03:45.959
But today, I play
 an even more important role --

03:45.993 --> 03:47.595
welcoming you to jury duty.

03:48.762 --> 03:50.564
Hello?

03:50.598 --> 03:53.133
It's for you.

03:53.166 --> 03:54.435
Justice is calling.

03:54.468 --> 03:55.936
[ Sighs heavily ]

03:55.969 --> 03:57.471
You want a tip?

03:57.505 --> 03:59.273
When the lawyers
ask you questions,

03:59.307 --> 04:00.974
just, uh, say that you watch
a lot of crime shows

04:01.008 --> 04:02.242
like "L.A. Law."

04:02.276 --> 04:03.711
They'll think
you're a real know-it-all

04:03.744 --> 04:05.313
who won't convict anybody
without DNA evidence,

04:05.346 --> 04:06.747
and then the lawyers
will just send you home.

04:13.487 --> 04:14.622
According to this,

04:14.655 --> 04:16.923
the Tamagotchi will beep
when it needs attention,

04:16.957 --> 04:19.293
at which point, its owner should
press a button to feed it,

04:19.327 --> 04:20.827
play with it,
or clean up its poop.

04:20.861 --> 04:22.463
It poops?

04:22.496 --> 04:24.465
Little black dots
with stink lines.

04:24.498 --> 04:25.466
Mm-hmm.

04:25.499 --> 04:27.668
If you don't
clean them up,

04:27.701 --> 04:30.638
the Tamagotchi
will get sick and die.

04:30.671 --> 04:32.272
Raising Jerry's
gonna be a lot of work.

04:32.306 --> 04:33.741
We'll do it together.

04:33.774 --> 04:36.009
We'll be the best moms
since Mom.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.978
Some days
you're the dog.

04:38.011 --> 04:39.980
Some days
you're the hydrant.

04:40.013 --> 04:41.615
What's wrong?

04:41.649 --> 04:44.852
Allison's making us see the new
"Romeo and Juliet" movie.

04:44.885 --> 04:47.588
Doesn't she know
that "Space Jam" just came out?

04:47.621 --> 04:49.623
Allison likes Shakespeare?
[ Chuckles ]

04:49.657 --> 04:52.793
But soft, what light
through yonder breaks?

04:52.826 --> 04:53.827
[ Romantic music plays ]

04:53.861 --> 04:57.631
It is the east,
and Juliet is the sun.

04:57.665 --> 05:00.634
Dad, that's the whitest
you've ever sounded.

05:00.668 --> 05:02.002
It's Shakespeare,
Eddie.

05:02.035 --> 05:03.270
It's poetry.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.705
You know
what's poetry?

05:04.738 --> 05:07.708
Michael Jordan teaming up with
Bugs Bunny to save the universe.

05:07.741 --> 05:09.543
If Allison wants
to see "Romeo and Juliet,"

05:09.577 --> 05:11.144
you should suck it up
and go.

05:11.178 --> 05:13.714
When you care about someone,
you have to make sacrifices.

05:13.747 --> 05:14.848
I guess.

05:14.882 --> 05:16.049
Tell you what,

05:16.083 --> 05:17.317
I'll give you and Allison
a ride to the movie.

05:17.351 --> 05:18.486
Seriously?

05:18.519 --> 05:20.053
Yeah.

05:20.087 --> 05:22.623
Think of me as your coachman,
spiriting you and your beloved

05:22.656 --> 05:24.525
through the ivory gates
of Verona.

05:24.558 --> 05:26.326
I don't understand
a word of that,

05:26.360 --> 05:27.828
but thanks
for the ride.

05:27.861 --> 05:29.563
[ "Law & Order" notes play ]

05:29.597 --> 05:31.198
Ma'am, you said
that serving on this jury

05:31.231 --> 05:32.466
would cause undue hardship.

05:32.500 --> 05:33.534
Can you elaborate?

05:33.567 --> 05:35.636
I can't be away from home
all day

05:35.669 --> 05:38.305
because I have to feed
my lizards, Thelma and Louise.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.007
Very well.
You're dismissed.

05:40.040 --> 05:41.475
[ Sighs ]

05:41.509 --> 05:42.910
[ Sighs ]

05:42.943 --> 05:44.912
Jessica Hu-wang?

05:44.945 --> 05:47.047
Huang.

05:47.080 --> 05:49.383
**

05:49.417 --> 05:50.684
Thank you
for joining us today.

05:50.718 --> 05:52.486
Is there any reason
why you can't be

05:52.520 --> 05:54.021
a fair
and unbiased juror?

05:54.054 --> 05:55.255
Yes.

05:55.288 --> 05:57.257
Because "L.A. Law."

05:57.290 --> 05:59.159
**

05:59.192 --> 06:00.360
Excuse me?

06:00.394 --> 06:02.763
It's my favorite show.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.565
Is that so?

06:04.598 --> 06:05.799
Who's your
favorite character?

06:07.034 --> 06:09.870
Mine's Victor Sifuentes.

06:09.903 --> 06:12.039
I've always fashioned myself
a young Corbin Bernsen.

06:12.072 --> 06:14.508
He's so kind
to his chubby assistant.

06:14.542 --> 06:16.944
Excuse me,
but I'm not going to let you two

06:16.977 --> 06:18.546
prattle on
about "L.A. Law".

06:19.713 --> 06:22.249
And not mention Benny.

06:22.282 --> 06:24.217
Benny!
I love Benny.

06:24.251 --> 06:25.719
[ Laughter ]

06:25.753 --> 06:27.621
Mrs. Hoo-ang, you sound
just like the type of person

06:27.655 --> 06:28.622
we're looking for.

06:28.656 --> 06:30.390
Welcome to jury duty.

06:30.424 --> 06:31.459
[ Sighs ]

06:36.129 --> 06:37.631
Great advice,
"L.A. Law."

06:37.665 --> 06:39.266
Thanks to you,
I'm stuck doing jury duty.

06:39.299 --> 06:42.069
Hey, you never take a swing,
you never hit a home run, right?

06:42.102 --> 06:44.037
You know, I used to hate
jury duty, too.

06:44.071 --> 06:46.440
Then, I accidentally spit
my chewing gum on the sidewalk

06:46.474 --> 06:48.108
during a trip
to Singapore.

06:48.141 --> 06:51.144
They caned my fanny
until it was red as an apple.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.747
After that,
I had a whole new appreciation

06:53.781 --> 06:55.115
for the American
legal system.

06:55.148 --> 06:56.283
[ All murmuring ]

06:56.316 --> 06:59.720
Oh, uh, they left us
an information sheet.

06:59.753 --> 07:00.821
According to this,

07:00.854 --> 07:02.956
we are supposed to elect
a jury foreperson.

07:02.990 --> 07:04.558
Foreperson --
what's that?

07:04.592 --> 07:06.126
Oh, a foreperson
takes attendance,

07:06.159 --> 07:07.895
they preside
over deliberations,

07:07.928 --> 07:10.163
and they speak on behalf
of the jury in the courtroom.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.499
It's sort of like
the boss of the jury.

07:11.532 --> 07:13.233
Jury Boss.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.267
I would like
to volunteer.

07:14.301 --> 07:15.736
I nominate Harvey.

07:15.769 --> 07:18.506
Well,
I don't know you from Adam,

07:18.539 --> 07:20.107
but you seem like
a nice fella

07:20.140 --> 07:21.341
and I like
the shape of your head.

07:21.374 --> 07:22.510
All in favor?

07:22.543 --> 07:24.311
Aye.

07:24.344 --> 07:27.515
[ Chuckles ] Aw, shucks, guys.
Thanks, everyone.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.116
Yay!
Congratulations, man.

07:29.149 --> 07:30.818
Thank you so much.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.786
**

07:32.820 --> 07:33.854
Hi, boys.

07:33.887 --> 07:37.457
Oh, my God!
Who's this little munchkin?

07:37.491 --> 07:39.793
Evan: That's Jerry.
He's our Tamagotchi.

07:39.827 --> 07:41.829
I read about these
in my anime magazine.

07:41.862 --> 07:44.164
I see Jerry has already reached
his Marutchi phase,

07:44.197 --> 07:45.699
having evolved
from a Babytchi.

07:45.733 --> 07:47.768
They grow up so fast,
don't they?

07:47.801 --> 07:49.002
Aww.I know.
[ Tamagotchi beeps ]

07:49.036 --> 07:50.437
[ Gasps ]
He made a boom-boom!

07:50.470 --> 07:52.005
Aww!Aww!
Aww!Aww!

07:52.039 --> 07:53.841
Reporter: It's really gonna be
 beautiful...

07:53.874 --> 07:55.809
You should see the people
on this jury, Louis.

07:55.843 --> 07:57.110
They're the only thing

07:57.144 --> 07:59.479
keeping a criminal
from walking the streets,

07:59.513 --> 08:01.682
and they spend 25 minutes
trying to figure out

08:01.715 --> 08:03.316
how to open up
a window.

08:03.350 --> 08:07.220
I can't believe
I wasn't picked for Jury Boss.

08:07.254 --> 08:09.557
I thought you didn't
 want to do jury duty.

08:09.590 --> 08:11.458
Now you want
 more responsibility?

08:11.491 --> 08:13.460
If I'm going to be stuck
on a jury,

08:13.493 --> 08:17.698
I want to be in charge,
not Harvey.

08:17.731 --> 08:20.033
He looks like a giant baby
with a beard.

08:20.067 --> 08:22.035
Hark!

08:22.069 --> 08:24.572
Is this a fly gentleman
I see before me?

08:24.605 --> 08:26.707
I can't believe I have to sit
through a whole movie of that.

08:26.740 --> 08:28.375
Well,
knock it all you want, Eddie,

08:28.408 --> 08:29.910
but the ladies
love Shakespeare.

08:29.943 --> 08:30.978
Just ask your mother.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.246
[ Chuckles ]
[ Door opens ]

08:33.280 --> 08:35.248
Your chariot awaits,
my liege.

08:35.282 --> 08:37.851
Huh?
Let's go.

08:37.885 --> 08:41.589
**

08:43.289 --> 08:44.424
Honk the horn.

08:44.457 --> 08:46.660
Are you a goose?
What?

08:46.694 --> 08:47.661
Geese honk.

08:47.695 --> 08:49.362
Gentlemen go
to the door.

08:49.396 --> 08:52.532
[ Sighs ]

08:55.402 --> 08:57.270
[ Knock on door ]

08:57.304 --> 08:58.606
Nice house.

09:01.141 --> 09:03.744
Hi, Eddie.
Hi, Mr. Huang.
Hi, Allison.

09:03.777 --> 09:04.845
Hi there, Eddie.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.247
You must be Eddie's dad.
Hi. Gary Olsen.

09:07.280 --> 09:08.515
Hi. I'm Louis.

09:08.548 --> 09:09.917
I just wanted
to introduce myself

09:09.950 --> 09:11.619
and let you know your daughter
will be in good hands.

09:11.652 --> 09:13.887
We're going to see the new
"Romeo and Juliet" movie.

09:13.921 --> 09:14.922
Really?

09:14.955 --> 09:16.690
I hear that's a hip,
modern remake

09:16.724 --> 09:18.558
set in the town
of Verona Beach?

09:18.592 --> 09:20.728
[ Laughs ]
Are you a Shakespeare fan, Gary?

09:20.761 --> 09:22.262
Been a Bardhead
since college.

09:22.295 --> 09:24.197
Me, too, Brute!

09:24.231 --> 09:26.066
[ Laughs ]

09:26.099 --> 09:28.235
Hey, since I'm driving the kids
to the movie,

09:28.268 --> 09:29.970
why don't you come along?
We'll all see it together.

09:30.003 --> 09:31.304
Uh, Dad...

09:31.338 --> 09:34.107
Really?
No. I'd hate to impose.

09:34.141 --> 09:37.277
What fates impose,
that men must needs abide --

09:37.310 --> 09:40.080
Both: It boots not to resist
both wind and tide.

09:40.113 --> 09:41.214
I'll get my coat.

09:41.248 --> 09:44.151
**

09:45.853 --> 09:48.155
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]

09:48.188 --> 09:49.356
[ Beeping stops ]

09:51.358 --> 09:52.993
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]

09:53.026 --> 09:53.961
[ Beeping stops ]

09:55.362 --> 09:56.897
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]
[ Sighs ]

09:56.930 --> 09:59.800
I've read the same sentence
like 20 times.

09:59.833 --> 10:02.836
Am I ever gonna find out
where the red fern grows?

10:02.870 --> 10:03.971
Let's take turns.

10:04.004 --> 10:05.839
We'll watch Jerry
in 30-minute shifts

10:05.873 --> 10:07.641
so the other person
can concentrate

10:07.675 --> 10:09.076
on finishing
their homework.

10:09.109 --> 10:10.443
That's a great idea.

10:10.477 --> 10:12.179
What do you think,
Jerry?

10:12.212 --> 10:13.847
Is that
a good idea?

10:13.881 --> 10:15.448
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]
I'll take that poop
as a yes.

10:16.684 --> 10:19.820
Benvolio:
 Tybalt hath sent a letter
 to his father's house.

10:19.853 --> 10:22.022
Mercutio:
 A challenge on my life.

10:22.055 --> 10:24.257
Louis: Mercutio,
thou oughtn't go in there!

10:24.291 --> 10:26.593
It's a trap,
me thinks!

10:26.626 --> 10:28.161
[ Both laugh ]

10:28.195 --> 10:30.664
[ Whispering ]
Can I have some Goobers?

10:30.698 --> 10:33.333
[ Whispering ] Our dads --
Our dads took them.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.368
Hey, Gary, Goober me.

10:35.402 --> 10:36.870
Oh, yeah.

10:36.904 --> 10:38.471
Oh, wait.
Let me mix it in.

10:38.505 --> 10:39.673
Mix it up.
[ Laughs ]

10:39.707 --> 10:41.709
[ Chatter ]

10:42.242 --> 10:43.844
Call to order.

10:43.877 --> 10:47.447
Case number 25772, State
of Florida versus Samuel Seaver,

10:47.480 --> 10:51.184
charged with eight counts
of arson in the second degree.

10:51.218 --> 10:54.287
But first, I have
an important matter to discuss.

10:54.321 --> 10:57.891
It's come to my attention
that a note was distributed

10:57.925 --> 11:00.327
amongst the jury,
along with a gift.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.329
Bailiff Dan.

11:02.362 --> 11:04.397
**

11:04.431 --> 11:07.400
"We need a new Jury Boss.

11:07.434 --> 11:10.137
Harvey is weak. Here's a gift."

11:10.170 --> 11:14.207
Normally, I would send all
of you home and seat new jury,

11:14.241 --> 11:16.243
but I'm planning
to run for office

11:16.276 --> 11:18.846
and I don't want to cost
the taxpayers any more money.

11:18.879 --> 11:21.381
Any attempt
to bribe your fellow juror

11:21.414 --> 11:24.417
will result in all of you
being held in contempt!

11:24.451 --> 11:27.921
Bailiff,
please collect the bribes.

11:36.063 --> 11:39.066
Harvey ate my orange.

11:39.099 --> 11:40.267
No.

11:43.570 --> 11:46.039
So, did you like
the movie?

11:46.073 --> 11:47.941
The gangsters were a'ight,
but most of the time,

11:47.975 --> 11:49.209
I had no idea
what was happening.

11:49.242 --> 11:51.678
Well,
 I liked it.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.446
In fact, it might be
my favorite movie of all time.

11:55.382 --> 11:58.085
E-Eddie,
do you ever get bored?

11:58.118 --> 12:00.053
I'm bored now,
thanks to this homework.

12:00.087 --> 12:02.722
No.
I mean bored with us.

12:02.756 --> 12:04.057
Us?
What are you talking about?

12:04.091 --> 12:05.425
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:05.458 --> 12:08.896
My dad's not supposed to
pick me up for another hour.

12:08.929 --> 12:11.064
Louis.

12:11.098 --> 12:12.399
Thought I'd come by
a little early.

12:12.432 --> 12:15.769
You mentioned you knew your way
around the old six-string.

12:15.803 --> 12:17.771
Any chance you'd be up
for a jam sesh?

12:19.406 --> 12:20.707
* If you

12:20.740 --> 12:22.709
* Like to tell me maybe

12:22.742 --> 12:24.077
* Just go ahead now

12:24.111 --> 12:25.278
* If you

12:25.312 --> 12:27.280
* Want to
buy me flowers *

12:27.314 --> 12:28.916
* Just go ahead now

12:28.949 --> 12:33.253
Yeah!
[ Vocalizing ]

12:33.286 --> 12:37.124
[ Both scatting ]

12:37.157 --> 12:40.627
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]

12:43.296 --> 12:45.732
Evan,
feed Jerry.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.901
I just did.
It's your turn.

12:47.935 --> 12:49.502
[ Beeping continues ]

12:49.536 --> 12:50.971
[ Pounding on wall ]

12:52.672 --> 12:54.975
Ugh!

12:55.008 --> 12:57.945
At least someone
will be rested tomorrow.

12:59.712 --> 13:00.848
[ Tamagotchi beeps ]

13:00.881 --> 13:02.415
Evan,
that's my calculator.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.284
[ Beeping continues ]

13:04.317 --> 13:05.652
[ Dialing ]

13:06.553 --> 13:07.787
[ Ringing ]

13:07.821 --> 13:09.857
Hello?
Hey, it's me.

13:09.890 --> 13:11.324
Hey, I'm glad
you called.

13:11.358 --> 13:12.259
We need to talk.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.626
Oh.

13:13.660 --> 13:15.128
Eddie, you know
I think you're great,

13:15.162 --> 13:17.464
and going out with you
this past year

13:17.497 --> 13:19.332
has been really,
really cool,

13:19.366 --> 13:21.634
but lately,
things have felt...

13:21.668 --> 13:22.970
different.

13:23.003 --> 13:24.537
It's like
somewhere along the line,

13:24.571 --> 13:26.006
we stopped having fun.

13:26.039 --> 13:27.841
That's not
how it should be.

13:27.875 --> 13:29.509
I mean,
look at our dads.

13:29.542 --> 13:30.844
Our dads?

13:30.878 --> 13:32.612
Do you see
how much fun they have?

13:32.645 --> 13:35.148
It reminded me
of how it used to be with us,

13:35.182 --> 13:37.650
back when things
were new and exciting.

13:37.684 --> 13:39.953
Face it, Eddie,
we've fallen into a rut.

13:39.987 --> 13:42.022
Is it a rut?
Or a groove?

13:42.055 --> 13:44.624
I think
we need to take a break.

13:44.657 --> 13:46.159
A break?
Allison, I --
[ Click ]

13:46.193 --> 13:47.794
Hey, guys,
uh, sorry to interrupt,

13:47.827 --> 13:49.162
but are you
almost done?

13:49.196 --> 13:51.364
I was hoping
Allison could put Gary on.

13:51.398 --> 13:53.166
Sorry, Eddie.

13:53.200 --> 13:54.301
Dad!

13:54.334 --> 13:55.702
[ Click ]
Hello?

13:55.735 --> 13:58.371
Hey, man, I picked up the guitar
tab for "Sultans of Swing."

13:58.405 --> 13:59.973
Yes, you did!

14:00.007 --> 14:02.009
[ Laughs ]

14:03.710 --> 14:05.412
**

14:05.445 --> 14:06.346
[ Sighs ]

14:12.752 --> 14:15.655
Well, those are some interesting
closing arguments,

14:15.688 --> 14:18.858
but given the witnesses who saw
the defendant light the fire

14:18.892 --> 14:21.561
and the footage of him dancing
around the flames afterwards,

14:21.594 --> 14:23.931
I'd say this is a pretty
open-and-shut case.

14:23.964 --> 14:25.265
So,
unless there are any questions,

14:25.298 --> 14:26.499
I reckon
we can just go ahead and vote.

14:26.533 --> 14:28.068
I have
a question.

14:28.868 --> 14:31.571
Why wasn't I
made Jury Boss?

14:34.141 --> 14:35.508
**

14:35.542 --> 14:36.776
Louis:
Uh, great news.

14:36.809 --> 14:37.911
The community theatre's

14:37.945 --> 14:39.779
doing Shakespeare in the Park
this weekend.

14:39.812 --> 14:41.881
Hope you and Allison
don't have any plans.

14:41.915 --> 14:44.084
We'll bring Gary.
Yeah.
That's not gonna happen.

14:45.385 --> 14:47.087
Me and Allison
are taking a break.

14:47.120 --> 14:50.057
What? Since when?
I thought you guys were solid.

14:50.090 --> 14:51.558
It's like
she got sick of me.

14:51.591 --> 14:53.126
She said
we were in a rut.

14:53.160 --> 14:55.929
A rut?
Or a groove?

14:55.963 --> 14:58.098
That's what I said,
but she wasn't hearing it.

14:58.131 --> 15:00.867
She said
that you and Gary had more fun.

15:00.900 --> 15:02.535
Maybe she has
a point.

15:02.569 --> 15:04.437
If our dads get along
better than we do,

15:04.471 --> 15:05.905
what does that say
about us?

15:05.939 --> 15:09.977
**

15:10.010 --> 15:11.979
Jessica: Because at the end
of the day,

15:12.012 --> 15:15.215
this is about
getting to the truth!

15:15.248 --> 15:19.052
Harvey claims
that he visited Singapore,

15:19.086 --> 15:21.454
yet today, he had a peanut
butter and jelly sandwich,

15:21.488 --> 15:24.557
even though there's a perfectly
good noodle shop next door.

15:24.591 --> 15:26.826
My wife
packed me a sandwich.

15:26.859 --> 15:28.895
Alleged wife.

15:28.928 --> 15:30.163
[ Sighs ]

15:30.197 --> 15:32.832
This isn't personal.

15:32.865 --> 15:34.801
I like Harvey.

15:34.834 --> 15:39.439
But is he really
Jury Boss material?

15:41.508 --> 15:43.676
So tense.

15:43.710 --> 15:44.811
Too tense?

15:44.844 --> 15:46.846
I mean,
you decide.

15:46.879 --> 15:48.648
Oh, for God's sake!

15:48.681 --> 15:50.450
It's been hours!

15:50.483 --> 15:52.352
Don't you see
what's happening?

15:52.385 --> 15:55.222
She's holding us hostage!

15:56.823 --> 15:57.924
Aah!

15:57.957 --> 16:01.161
Why won't
these windows open?!

16:01.194 --> 16:02.529
O-Okay, okay.

16:02.562 --> 16:05.132
Uh, Jessica,
may I have a word? Please?

16:05.165 --> 16:06.366
**

16:06.399 --> 16:08.435
If we let you
be jury foreperson,

16:08.468 --> 16:11.104
will you just cast your vote
so we can go home?

16:11.138 --> 16:14.874
It would be my first act
as Jury Boss.

16:14.907 --> 16:16.776
Harvey: Okay, so,
when the judge asks,

16:16.809 --> 16:19.946
you just read the verdict,
and then we can all go.

16:19.979 --> 16:22.782
Thank you,
Jury Minion.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.651
Dan: All rise!

16:26.853 --> 16:28.355
You may be seated.

16:29.689 --> 16:31.991
I understand the jury
has reached a verdict?

16:32.025 --> 16:33.560
Why isn't Harvey
sitting in the --

16:33.593 --> 16:35.162
Harvey had
a scratchy throat,

16:35.195 --> 16:37.497
so I'm filling in
as Madame Foreperson.

16:38.765 --> 16:40.367
Very well.

16:40.400 --> 16:43.036
Would our new foreperson please
read the verdict to the court?

16:43.070 --> 16:45.805
Yes,
Your Honor.

16:45.838 --> 16:48.375
**

16:48.408 --> 16:52.712
We, the jury,
find the defendant...

16:52.745 --> 16:53.913
guilty.

16:53.946 --> 16:54.914
[ Spectators murmur ]

16:54.947 --> 16:57.550
Stop burning things,
you weirdo.

16:57.584 --> 16:59.919
I hated you
the moment I saw you.

16:59.952 --> 17:01.988
That's a mistrial.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.590
[ Spectators murmur ]
What?

17:03.623 --> 17:05.492
He's obviously guilty!

17:05.525 --> 17:08.095
Look at him!
Look at his face!

17:08.127 --> 17:09.862
Innocent people
don't have hair like that!

17:13.900 --> 17:16.336
Louis!

17:16.368 --> 17:18.271
I was just
about to call you.

17:18.305 --> 17:20.873
Any interest
in going to Medieval Times

17:20.906 --> 17:23.910
and ordering drumsticks
in iambic pentameter?

17:23.943 --> 17:25.912
[ In iambic pentameter ]
That sounds so great to me.

17:25.944 --> 17:27.414
[ Chuckles ]
[ Normal voice ]
But I can't.

17:27.446 --> 17:29.048
Not today.

17:29.082 --> 17:31.050
Not ever.

17:31.084 --> 17:33.186
It's because
of Eddie and Allison, isn't it?

17:33.220 --> 17:35.222
Darn it!
I knew something was up.

17:35.255 --> 17:37.424
I haven't seen Allison
this upset

17:37.457 --> 17:39.859
since those wildebeests
trampled Mufasa.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.561
It's because of us,
Gary.

17:41.594 --> 17:43.763
For whatever reason,
our connection

17:43.796 --> 17:46.633
has caused Eddie and Allison
to doubt theirs.

17:46.666 --> 17:48.801
We're tearing
our houses apart,

17:48.835 --> 17:51.404
just like
the Montagues and Capulets.

17:51.438 --> 17:54.073
Are you saying --
I'm afraid
we can't be friends anymore.

17:54.107 --> 17:56.476
That really is
too bad.

17:56.509 --> 17:59.446
I liked
having such a cool friend.

17:59.479 --> 18:00.713
Me, too.

18:00.747 --> 18:03.550
But when you care
about someone,

18:03.583 --> 18:05.618
you have to
make sacrifices.

18:05.652 --> 18:06.986
**

18:08.655 --> 18:10.957
Shakespeare invented this,
you know?

18:10.990 --> 18:12.792
He called it
"the hand hug."

18:12.825 --> 18:14.661
Because men
couldn't hug back then.

18:14.694 --> 18:15.662
Right.

18:15.695 --> 18:17.497
Because men
couldn't hug.

18:17.530 --> 18:19.599
**

18:21.100 --> 18:23.636
I can't believe
I slept through Roman numerals.

18:23.670 --> 18:25.838
Now I'm never gonna know
what Super Bowl it is.

18:25.872 --> 18:27.774
You're tired?

18:27.807 --> 18:28.941
In Karate Club,

18:28.975 --> 18:30.343
I accidentally
kicked a kid in the face.

18:30.377 --> 18:31.978
That's nice.

18:32.011 --> 18:34.314
I can't remember the last time
I had a chance to exercise.

18:34.347 --> 18:35.815
[ Tamagotchi beeping ]
You have it easy.

18:35.848 --> 18:37.016
All you do is,

18:37.049 --> 18:38.418
you just ply Jerry with food
to keep him quiet.

18:38.451 --> 18:40.420
I feed him
because he's hungry.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.255
All you do
is play with him!

18:42.289 --> 18:43.756
I have to
play with him.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.325
Otherwise,
he'd be a fat blob.

18:45.358 --> 18:47.460
Don't you dare
call Jerry fat!
I didn't.

18:47.494 --> 18:48.928
You're putting words
in my mouth,

18:48.961 --> 18:50.863
just like you put
empty calories in Jerry's.

18:50.897 --> 18:52.432
You take that back!
I will not!

18:52.465 --> 18:53.433
[ Tamagotchi beeps ]

18:53.466 --> 18:56.135
[ Tamagotchi flatlines ]

18:56.169 --> 18:57.304
Jerry?

18:57.337 --> 19:00.207
**

19:00.240 --> 19:02.442
Having a snack?

19:02.475 --> 19:03.976
Why not?

19:04.010 --> 19:05.778
Now that I'm single,
I don't have to watch my figure.

19:05.812 --> 19:06.979
You were watching
your figure?

19:07.013 --> 19:09.216
You know,
your situation with Allison

19:09.249 --> 19:11.184
reminds me
of an old love story.

19:11.218 --> 19:13.520
Dad, please, I do not want
to hear any more Shakespeare.

19:13.553 --> 19:14.987
I'm not talking
about Shakespeare.

19:15.021 --> 19:16.989
I'm talking about
when I was dating your mom.

19:17.023 --> 19:19.125
I really wanted
to impress her,

19:19.158 --> 19:21.294
so I used to serenade her
with my guitar.

19:21.328 --> 19:24.531
But after a while, I could tell
she was getting sick of it.

19:24.564 --> 19:26.333
[ Chuckles ]
I know, crazy, right?

19:26.366 --> 19:28.335
So, I switched it up,

19:28.368 --> 19:30.503
and I started
reading her Shakespeare instead.

19:30.537 --> 19:31.904
I kept it fresh,

19:31.938 --> 19:33.973
and that's what you need
to do with Allison.

19:34.006 --> 19:37.009
You have to show her
things can still be unexpected

19:37.043 --> 19:39.746
and spontaneous, just like
it was at the beginning.

19:39.779 --> 19:41.714
[ Crunch ]

19:43.216 --> 19:45.151
[ Knock on door ]

19:45.184 --> 19:46.886
Eddie?

19:46.919 --> 19:48.355
Allison, there's something
I have to tell you.

19:48.388 --> 19:50.022
I'm sorry I've been
so boring lately.

19:50.056 --> 19:51.691
It's just
you're so chill,

19:51.724 --> 19:54.026
and I feel like
I can be myself around you.

19:54.060 --> 19:55.862
And to be honest,
myself is a little lazy.

19:57.096 --> 19:58.998
So, I'm going to make
more of an effort

19:59.031 --> 20:00.667
to show that I appreciate you,
because I do!

20:00.700 --> 20:02.602
Get your coat,
girl.

20:02.635 --> 20:04.036
We're gonna go see
"Romeo and Juliet."

20:04.070 --> 20:05.238
But we already
saw it.

20:05.272 --> 20:06.706
I know!
I'm being spontaneous!

20:06.739 --> 20:08.107
You're surprised,
right?

20:08.140 --> 20:09.442
You didn't
see that coming.

20:09.476 --> 20:11.043
[ Chuckles ]

20:11.077 --> 20:14.514
**

20:14.547 --> 20:16.716
[ Intro to Spin Doctors'
 "Two Princes" plays ]

20:16.749 --> 20:18.184
Deejay:
 We've got a dedication

20:18.217 --> 20:20.353
going out
 to a special coachman.

20:20.387 --> 20:23.189
It says,
 "From a Capulet to a Montague,

20:23.222 --> 20:26.225
I'll never forget
 when we were 'Two Princes'."

20:26.259 --> 20:28.795
* One, two,
 princes kneel before you *

20:28.828 --> 20:30.930
* That's what I said, now *

20:30.963 --> 20:33.566
* Princes,
Princes who adore you *

20:33.600 --> 20:34.734
* Just go ahead, now

20:34.767 --> 20:35.768
* One has...

20:41.408 --> 20:45.878
[ Somber music plays ]

20:45.912 --> 20:46.979
[ Sighs ]

20:47.013 --> 20:49.882
No parent should outlive
their Tamagotchi.

20:49.916 --> 20:51.884
It was only
a few extra words.

20:51.918 --> 20:55.087
I don't understand why they
have to redo the whole trial.

20:55.121 --> 20:56.756
To be honest,

20:56.789 --> 20:58.725
I'm surprised you did jury duty
in the first place.

20:58.758 --> 20:59.892
What do you mean?

20:59.926 --> 21:01.294
You're not a citizen yet,
Jessica.

21:02.429 --> 21:03.963
They must've sent you
the summons by accident.

21:03.996 --> 21:05.832
All you had to do was say
you're here on a green card,

21:05.865 --> 21:07.099
and you could've
gotten out of it.

21:07.133 --> 21:08.935
Ugh.

21:10.603 --> 21:12.972
Mom's really broken up
about Jerry.

21:13.005 --> 21:14.273
I didn't even know
she knew him.

21:14.307 --> 21:16.075
[ Sighs ]

21:16.108 --> 21:17.644
[ Tamagotchi beeps faintly ]

21:17.677 --> 21:19.446
Did you
hear something?

21:21.047 --> 21:22.482
[ Tamagotchi beeps ]

21:23.516 --> 21:25.352
No.
